<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Super simple x86app launcher]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1062&amp;p=5537#p5537"><![CDATA[
Thanks for info on Launchy. Pass though. I Like point and click.<br /><br />Did find a couple more that get to bare bone launchers, but CSM still da best. <br /><br />I found a sneaky way of keeping the Win 7 style menu contained without flyout,<br />when all the parked links are not shown. <br />Duplicated one of the current items into a custom.<br />GauravK got me thinking from a post of his about the ampersand.<br />I put &quot;&amp;&quot; as the label. The menu box is now closed with its frame on right side.<br />It's a little wider but still ok.<br />Still showed an outline of a parked link box when hovered over, and location error when clicked on.<br />I put desktop toggle as a link<br />%windir%\explorer.exe shell:::{3080F90D-D7AD-11D9-BD98-0000947B0257} <br />so if I do click by mistake, nothing happens.<br /><br />So now I have two launch menu versions of linking to WinX.<br />The old classic and the new classic. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Fri Aug 09, 2013 11:33 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
