<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[juniper7]]></name></author>
<updated>2013-08-07T17:26:51-07:00</updated>
<published>2013-08-07T17:26:51-07:00</published>
<id>http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1062&amp;p=5479#p5479</id>
<link href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1062&amp;p=5479#p5479"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Super simple x86app launcher]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1062&amp;p=5479#p5479"><![CDATA[
CSM is a great menu for the masses, and the tinkerers.<br /><br />Would Ivo ever have time to make a little sibling menu, <br />with only x86 application launcher, for other people?<br />Like the one anyone can make in the taskbar toolbar, <br />but with a few changes, for the better?<br /><br />It would be able to blend the two Win 8 start menu folders using <br />the virtual folder shell:::{7be9d83c-a729-4d97-b5a7-1b7313c39e0a} <br />and keep the expanding menu in a box, like Windows Vista/7.<br />That way, everything is available within a few inches of curser.<br />Throw in a dedicated launch button anywhere on taskbar. <br />That's about it. A real simple, fast and clean one.<br /><br />I tried playing with 3.9.0 beta. <br />Almost got it with Win7 style, but when I turned off lots of the permanent links, <br />then the menu flew away again across the screen, with all my installed programs. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /> <br /><br />There isn't much in the way of simple launchers out there on net.<br />The closest I could find, but not close enough are:<br /><br />7stacks.<br /><br />Can change it's icon and pin to taskbar. <br />Can't merge user and all menu folders, <br />unless done with copies in a folder, so won't update. <br />Some icons a no show.<br /><br />Handy Start Menu<br /><br />Can contain menu without flying away.<br />Icon no show problems.<br />Launch button only one place on taskbar.<br /><br />I 'll keep digging.<br />Still using CSM minimal menu linked with WinX on a daily basis, until something better comes along. Works fine.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Wed Aug 07, 2013 5:26 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
